{
  "_comment": [
    "Full baseline sweep at 4K context (2048 in / 2048 out) — the v7x",
    "stress test to expose v7x advantage over v6e.",
    "",
    "Three deliberate departures from llama3_8b_v7x_baseline_full.service:",
    "",
    "  1. Workload shape: 2048/2048 (vs 1800/128). 4K total context",
    "     per request stresses HBM-per-request more than the prefill-",
    "     heavy 1.9K case, which barely uses 1/4 of the 8K context",
    "     window. v7x s 96 GB HBM advantage starts mattering here.",
    "",
    "  2. MAX_NUM_SEQS swept {128, 1000}. 128 is the smoke / v6e-era",
    "     ceiling; 1000 lets the engine schedule as many in-flight as",
    "     v7xs HBM allows. vllm auto-caps the actual concurrency to",
    "     whatever fits (max_num_seqs is willingness, not pre-",
    "     allocation), so 1000 is safe to set even though 1000 seqs",
    "     at full max_model_len wouldnt fit. If the 1000 row throughputs",
    "     noticeably above 128 at the same MAX_NUM_BATCHED_TOKENS, we",
    "     have direct evidence v7xs HBM headroom converts to throughput.",
    "",
    "  3. MAX_NUM_BATCHED_TOKENS swept {4096, 10275}. 10275 is bm-infra s",
    "     v7x default — wider step budget = more amortized kernel",
    "     overhead per call.",
    "",
    "Combos: 4 (2 MAX_NUM_SEQS x 2 MAX_NUM_BATCHED_TOKENS).",
    "NUM_PROMPTS=1000 inherited from balanced_4k.workload.",
    "",
